OL,3,CJapanese people to all have same
OL,4,Csurname by 2531, study shows
OL,6,F"If everyone becomes Sato, we may have
OL,7,Fto be addressed by our first names or
OL,8,Fby numbers, I don't think that would
OL,9,Fbe a great world to live in,"
OL,10,FProfessor Yoshida said, according to
OL,11,Fthe Japanese newspaper Mainichi.
OL,13,F'Sato' is the most common surname in
OL,14,FJapan, reportedly making up 1.5% of
OL,15,Fthe population.
OL,17,FAccording to Prof Yoshida's study, the
OL,18,Fnumber of people with the surname Sato
OL,19,Fin the population increased by 1.0083%
OL,20,Fbetween 2022 and 2023.
