OL,3,CJapanese people to all have same
OL,4,Csurname by 2531, study shows
OL,6,FThe study was driven to promote
OL,7,Fawareness for Professor Yoshida's
OL,8,Finitiative - called the
OL,9,FThinkNameProject - which hopes to
OL,10,Faddress Japan's historic marriage laws.
OL,12,FJapan is the only country with a law
OL,13,Frequiring couples to adopt the same
OL,14,Fsurname once married.
OL,16,FThe 19th century law doesn't specify
OL,17,Fwhich spouse should change their
OL,18,Fsurname, but an overwhelming majority
OL,19,Fof women take their husband's.
